-- Australia shares dips 0.6 pct on oil woes & hostage incident
-- 
-- Mon Dec 15, 2014 12:20AM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 15 (Reuters) - Australian shares fell for a fifth straight session on Monday following a slide in oil prices, while deteriorating government finances and a hostage incident in Sydney further undermined sentiment.[ID:nL3N0TZ17E]

The S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> eased 33.4 points, or 0.6 percent, to 5,186.1 at the close of trade, pulling closer to a two-month low of 5,122.